main event: A radar operator observed three unidentified objects intercepted by two F-94s near Benton, PA on April 17, 1952.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 20 minutes at a speed of 210 knots,The radar return was strong but difficult to lock onto,The objects were observed at a distance of approximately 21 miles,The identification of the objects was not confirmed,The report states a B-17 was involved in the sighting.
